  "root_text": {
    "snp1.11:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.11 ",
    "snp1.11:0.2": "Vijayasutta ",
    "snp1.11:1.1": "Caraṁ vā yadi vā tiṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:1.2": "nisinno uda vā sayaṁ; ",
    "snp1.11:1.3": "Samiñjeti pasāreti, ",
    "snp1.11:1.4": "esā kāyassa iñjanā. ",
    "snp1.11:2.1": "Aṭṭhinahārusaṁyutto, ",
    "snp1.11:2.2": "tacamaṁsāvalepano; ",
    "snp1.11:2.3": "Chaviyā kāyo paṭicchanno, ",
    "snp1.11:2.4": "yathābhūtaṁ na dissati. ",
    "snp1.11:3.1": "Antapūro udarapūro, ",
    "snp1.11:3.2": "yakanapeḷassa vatthino; ",
    "snp1.11:3.3": "Hadayassa papphāsassa, ",
    "snp1.11:3.4": "vakkassa pihakassa ca. ",
    "snp1.11:4.1": "Siṅghāṇikāya kheḷassa, ",
    "snp1.11:4.2": "sedassa ca medassa ca; ",
    "snp1.11:4.3": "Lohitassa lasikāya, ",
    "snp1.11:4.4": "pittassa ca vasāya ca. ",
    "snp1.11:5.1": "Athassa navahi sotehi, ",
    "snp1.11:5.2": "asucī savati sabbadā; ",
    "snp1.11:5.3": "Akkhimhā akkhigūthako, ",
    "snp1.11:5.4": "kaṇṇamhā kaṇṇagūthako. ",
    "snp1.11:6.1": "Siṅghāṇikā ca nāsato, ",
    "snp1.11:6.2": "mukhena vamatekadā; ",
    "snp1.11:6.3": "Pittaṁ semhañca vamati, ",
    "snp1.11:6.4": "kāyamhā sedajallikā. ",
    "snp1.11:7.1": "Athassa susiraṁ sīsaṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:7.2": "matthaluṅgassa pūritaṁ; ",
    "snp1.11:7.3": "Subhato naṁ maññati bālo, ",
    "snp1.11:7.4": "avijjāya purakkhato. ",
    "snp1.11:8.1": "Yadā ca so mato seti, ",
    "snp1.11:8.2": "Uddhumāto vinīlako; ",
    "snp1.11:8.3": "Apaviddho susānasmiṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:8.4": "Anapekkhā honti ñātayo. ",
    "snp1.11:9.1": "Khādanti naṁ suvānā ca, ",
    "snp1.11:9.2": "siṅgālā ca vakā kimī; ",
    "snp1.11:9.3": "Kākā gijjhā ca khādanti, ",
    "snp1.11:9.4": "ye caññe santi pāṇino. ",
    "snp1.11:10.1": "Sutvāna buddhavacanaṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:10.2": "Bhikkhu paññāṇavā idha; ",
    "snp1.11:10.3": "So kho naṁ parijānāti, ",
    "snp1.11:10.4": "Yathābhūtañhi passati. ",
    "snp1.11:11.1": "Yathā idaṁ tathā etaṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:11.2": "Yathā etaṁ tathā idaṁ; ",
    "snp1.11:11.3": "Ajjhattañca bahiddhā ca, ",
    "snp1.11:11.4": "Kāye chandaṁ virājaye. ",
    "snp1.11:12.1": "Chandarāgaviratto so, ",
    "snp1.11:12.2": "Bhikkhu paññāṇavā idha; ",
    "snp1.11:12.3": "Ajjhagā amataṁ santiṁ, ",
    "snp1.11:12.4": "Nibbānaṁ padamaccutaṁ. ",
    "snp1.11:13.1": "Dvipādakoyaṁ asuci, ",
    "snp1.11:13.2": "Duggandho parihīrati; ",
    "snp1.11:13.3": "Nānākuṇapaparipūro, ",
    "snp1.11:13.4": "Vissavanto tato tato. ",
    "snp1.11:14.1": "Etādisena kāyena, ",
    "snp1.11:14.2": "Yo maññe uṇṇametave; ",
    "snp1.11:14.3": "Paraṁ vā avajāneyya, ",
    "snp1.11:14.4": "Kimaññatra adassanāti. ",
    "snp1.11:14.5": "Vijayasuttaṁ ekādasamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.11:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.11 ",
    "snp1.11:0.2": "Victory Over Desire for the Body ",
    "snp1.11:1.1": "Walking and standing, ",
    "snp1.11:1.2": "sitting and lying down, ",
    "snp1.11:1.3": "extending and contracting the limbs: ",
    "snp1.11:1.4": "these are the movements of the body. ",
    "snp1.11:2.1": "Linked together by bones and sinews, ",
    "snp1.11:2.2": "plastered over with flesh and hide, ",
    "snp1.11:2.3": "and covered by the skin, ",
    "snp1.11:2.4": "the body is not seen as it is. ",
    "snp1.11:3.1": "It’s full of guts and belly, ",
    "snp1.11:3.2": "liver and bladder, ",
    "snp1.11:3.3": "heart and lungs, ",
    "snp1.11:3.4": "kidney and spleen, ",
    "snp1.11:4.1": "spit and snot, ",
    "snp1.11:4.2": "sweat and fat, ",
    "snp1.11:4.3": "blood and synovial fluid, ",
    "snp1.11:4.4": "bile and grease. ",
    "snp1.11:5.1": "Then in nine streams ",
    "snp1.11:5.2": "the filth is always flowing. ",
    "snp1.11:5.3": "There is muck from the eyes, ",
    "snp1.11:5.4": "wax from the ears, ",
    "snp1.11:6.1": "and snot from the nostrils. ",
    "snp1.11:6.2": "The mouth sometimes vomits ",
    "snp1.11:6.3": "bile and sometimes phlegm. ",
    "snp1.11:6.4": "And from the body, sweat and waste. ",
    "snp1.11:7.1": "Then there is the hollow head ",
    "snp1.11:7.2": "all filled with brains. ",
    "snp1.11:7.3": "Governed by ignorance, ",
    "snp1.11:7.4": "the fool thinks it’s lovely. ",
    "snp1.11:8.1": "And when it lies dead, ",
    "snp1.11:8.2": "bloated and livid, ",
    "snp1.11:8.3": "dumped in a charnel ground, ",
    "snp1.11:8.4": "the relatives forget it. ",
    "snp1.11:9.1": "It’s devoured by dogs, ",
    "snp1.11:9.2": "by jackals, wolves, and worms. ",
    "snp1.11:9.3": "It’s devoured by crows and vultures, ",
    "snp1.11:9.4": "and any other creatures there. ",
    "snp1.11:10.1": "A wise mendicant here, ",
    "snp1.11:10.2": "having heard the Buddha’s words, ",
    "snp1.11:10.3": "fully understands it, ",
    "snp1.11:10.4": "for they see it as it is. ",
    "snp1.11:11.1": "“As this is, so is that, ",
    "snp1.11:11.2": "as that is, so is this.” ",
    "snp1.11:11.3": "They’d blanch desire for the body ",
    "snp1.11:11.4": "inside and out. ",
    "snp1.11:12.1": "That wise mendicant here ",
    "snp1.11:12.2": "rid of desire and lust, ",
    "snp1.11:12.3": "has found the peace free of death, ",
    "snp1.11:12.4": "extinguishment, the state that does not pass. ",
    "snp1.11:13.1": "This two-legged body is dirty and stinking, ",
    "snp1.11:13.2": "full of different carcasses, ",
    "snp1.11:13.3": "and oozing all over the place—",
    "snp1.11:13.4": "but still it is cherished! ",
    "snp1.11:14.1": "And if, on account of such a body, ",
    "snp1.11:14.2": "someone prides themselves ",
    "snp1.11:14.3": "or looks down on others—",
    "snp1.11:14.4": "what is that but a failure to see? "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp1.11:2.1": "Aṭṭhinahārusaṁyutto → aṭṭhinhārūhi saṁyutto (sya-all, mr); aṭṭhīnahārusaññutto (pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.11:3.2": "yakanapeḷassa → yakapeḷassa (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.11:9.1": "suvānā → suvāṇā (bj, sya-all); supāṇā (pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.11:9.2": "siṅgālā → sigālā (bj, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.11:13.1": "Dvipādakoyaṁ → dipādakoyaṁ (bj, sya-all, km, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.11:13.2": "parihīrati → parihārati (csp1ed) ",
    "snp1.11:14.2": "uṇṇametave → unnametave (?) "
  },
